sessions.title: Furnal Kickoff
sessions.description: The one and only panel you don't want to miss! Talented DJs from all over, are guaranteed to get your tails shaking, with non-stop beats!

sessions.title: Opening Ceremonies
sessions.description: The opening ceremonies and closing ceremonies

sessions.title: Fursuit Dancing 101
sessions.description: Thinking of taking your first steps at competing in the dance competition or floor wars? Join us to learn everything from dance fundamentals to handling critiques.

sessions.title: Macro/Micro Meetup
sessions.description: Furries come in all sizes, ranging from very tiny to immense.  Whether you like taking your dinner from the roof of a building or while hanging out on the head of a pin, come along and meet with other Furries of Unusual Size.

sessions.title: Tales from the Table: Intro to Board Games
sessions.description: Welcome to the tavern, traveller. Fancy a game? We have dice, cards, and many other ways to suit your fancy. Join Conreeaght as he goes through introductions to some board game archetypes and some briefs on how to play each. If you want to learn about the state of  board games, or want to meet new players to play with, then come join us and ROLL FOR INITIATIVE!!!

sessions.title: So This Is Your First Convention
sessions.description: Join Avalanche and friends for an educational talk on what to expect, social etiquette & behaviour at FE, and how to make the most out of this exciting weekend! A MUST for first-time con-goers, parents, and those joining us who are new to the fandom. Some of our more seasoned attendees may also learn a thing or two!

sessions.title: Storyboarding for Dummies
sessions.description: Want to learn to storyboard but don’t know where to start? Maybe you want to take your storytelling skills to the next level? Let Professor asagurble teach you a thing or two from storyboard basics to advanced tips and tricks used by board professionals.

sessions.title: Artemis Spaceship Bridge Simulator (Presented by Hacklab Toronto)
sessions.description:
Artemis is a real time Co-Op computer game. Players work together in the roles of Captain, Helm, Science, Communication, Engineering, and Weapon Control. Operate the ship, take on missions and defend against other hostile ships.

New and experienced players welcome. Drop in for a pick-up game, or register your crew for a group session.

Present by Hacklab Toronto
https://hacklab.to/

Artemis Spaceship Bridge Simulator
https://www.artemisspaceshipbridge.com/

sessions.title: Fursuit Games
sessions.description: Our annual Fursuit Games are your chance to amuse the host's team up with your squad of fluffs for some exhilarating games, a lot of laughs, and good times all around. Also egg.

sessions.title: Inflatable fun-times!
sessions.description: Ever see those cute big inflatable animals online around in the fandom and think "Hey, those look like alot of fun!"? Well now is your chance to see them in person! This panel will have big custom-made inflatable toys from creators such as Puffypaws, G&G, PhenodToy & Inflatable World which you can come interact with, sit on or take photos with! Come meet some inflatable enthusiasts of the fandom, ask questions, get pictures and have fun!

sessions.title: The Great Debate
sessions.description: This comedic panel pits two opinionated and funny individuals against each other in a live debate on a topic important to Furries. With 2 sets of debaters & 2 hilarious topics, they'll use their knowledge and humour to win over the audience who decides who wins each debate!

sessions.title: Effective Writing:  How to Make a Story Come Alive
sessions.description: Uncle Kage is a not only a scientist and a convention organizer, but he is also a writer  His short stories have been published by Daw Fantasy, Sofawolf Press, FurPlanet and others.  Here he presents tips and tricks for getting a reader's attention and for holding onto it until the last paragraph.  Spoiler: your English teacher was right!

sessions.title: How to finance your furry fascination
sessions.description: Would you like to easily save 250$ for every furry convention you will ever attend? Would you like to never have to worry about your budget when buying furry stuff? Managing your money doesn't have to make you miserable, come on down for a presentation so easy that even a simple moose can understand it!

sessions.title: Meet the GOHs
sessions.description: Join Furnal Equinox in meeting our GOHs.

sessions.title: Magic: The Gathering - Meet and Duel
sessions.description:
Calling all Magic: The Gathering players!

Looking to get your duel on and maybe make some new friends or, perhaps rivals? Then this open social gathering of like-minded Magic players is for you!

This casual event is for the Magic playing attendees of Furnal Equinox to meet other Magic: The Gathering enthusiasts and share battle strategies, trade or just find new folks to duel. All formats welcome, but Casual and Commander suggested.

This is social event with no host or lead and will take place at the reserved, rectangular tables located in the rear-most (Pier 5) section of the Lounge (Pier 4 & 5.)

sessions.title: Telestrations Party! - Open Game
sessions.description:
One part Pictionary, one part game of Telephone, it's Telestrations! The guess what you see and draw what you read party game!

This is an open game for anyone to join, whether you have you own group or are looking to play with new folks

Learn to play here:
https://youtu.be/OStOnMypEzo

Seats limited to 12 players per game on a first come basis. See lounge staff to check out Telestrations if game is not underway.

sessions.title: Pokémon Go Meetup!
sessions.description: Trainers!  Come gather to meet fellow trainers from across the globe to share friend codes, conduct some trades, and share knowledge with other players!  Whether you're a beginner or expert, come join us for some fun!

sessions.title: Long-Distance Relationships: Tips and Tricks to Make Them Work
sessions.description: Being in a Long Distance Relationship can seem daunting. But if the bond and love is strong, there is no hurdle that can't be overcome. Learn some tips to make them last regardless of the distance between you and your partner

sessions.description:

The in-person portal and the VRChat portal are both located in the same place:
2nd Floor, outside Pier 3

On the virtual side from VRChat, seek out the world called "The West Inn" made by Lilithe Lotor and join the session with the TailBass taidum bot to interact with everyone at the convention.

Instance links will be provided in the Furnal Equinox Discord and Telegram.

sessions.title: You and Me and D&D
sessions.description:
"Interactive Dungeons and Dragons one shot where the entire audience will (hopefully) work together to guide a singular character through an adventure!

All decisions that the character makes will be carried out via Telegram polls.
REMEMEBER TO BRING YOUR PHONES ADVENTURERS! :D"

sessions.title: Data Structures and Algorithms
sessions.description: Programmers with any amount of experience are welcome! We'll talk about different approaches to solving some of my favorite coding problems. Hopefully you (and possibly I) will learn a thing or two about algorithmic problem solving!

sessions.title: Maple's Jackbox Jam!
sessions.description: Want to put your creative skills to the test and play a fun game with other furs? Maple hosts a game of Jackbox Party Pack 5 & 7, and even if you don't want to straight up play (limited slots), the audience can join in!

sessions.title: Convention History - Cons Before and After Furries
sessions.description: Join us for a look at the over 80 year history of the convention scene from the early Worldcons to the modern virtual cons. We will look at the fandoms that shaped the earlier cons and paved the way for the furry conventions and what impact furries left on the overall con scene.

sessions.title: I Made a Fursuit and You Can Too
sessions.description: So you bought your fabric, stocked up on hot glue and downloaded the patterns. Feeling overwhelmed? Join me and I'll take you through what to expect, what went wrong, what went right, and how to muddle your way to the finish line. An informal panel and Q&A from a newly minted fursuit builder.

sessions.title: Furry Yoga
sessions.description:
"Feel the power of Furry Yoga! Furry Yoga is a free weekly program hosted by Fuzz Buttons & Muttsi705 that combines the power of entertainment & benefit of exercise together in a fuzzy combination!  Have fun while working out as Fuzz Buttons teaches you yoga in Fursuit!! 

The purpose of this is to spread Furry Yoga reach & also show off this new twist on the way people see Yoga in hopes they reach there goals!!
check out furryyoga.com for more information!"

sessions.title: Animation Industry Nightmares
sessions.description: Professional animators and other entertainment industry professionals tell horror stories of what happens behind the scenes. All light hearted of course! Silly assignments, stupid bosses and general Q&A for all that are curious about cartoons and how they're made!

sessions.title: Great Tavern Concert - Early Access - Accessibility
TMNT Shadows of the Past - Scenario Game
sessions.description: Always wanted to be a turtle, or Casey, or even Splinter? In this game depending what map and scenario you can!. ALL mini game so you can hold and see yourself as a character fighting off the foot, or bots, or whatever else the game dictates. One hour time slot but may be longer depending on the luck of dice and ninjas

sessions.title: Brief History of Transformation and Shapeshifting in Stories
sessions.description: This panel looks at the history of transformation, shapeshifting, and werecreatures in fiction, from ancient traditions and myths, to folklore and fables, to comics superheroes and anime, to modern day fiction and the furry fandom. We will look at the diverse manner in which human to animal transformation has been tackled, common tropes and themes. Hosted by Johns Hopkins University historian and Would've Bit You comic creator, Inanimorphs.

sessions.title: Sketch Book Swap
sessions.description: Bring your sketch book and a printed out reference sheet to the first Furnal equinox sketch book swap! Meet other artists in the community and get connected!  All skill levels welcome! Limited sketch books will be provided for those with none. But please bring your own if your able! To ensure sketch books can be returned after the event please add you mailing address to the first page.

sessions.title: Great Tavern Concert - Early Access - Benefactor/Supersponsor/Sponsor
The Great Tavern Concert
sessions.description: A concert event featuring two hours of pop and rock music from Avalanche (AKA Aric Zair), Xephyr, and Damiano's Elysium (Feat. Anubis). This show will get your blood pumping and your excitement rising as you take part in this unique blend of musical acts! Check out this awesome show, with some combined performances sure to blow you away!

sessions.title: Digital Art Painting Demo
sessions.description: In this short panel I'll be sharing insights into my workflow of my painting process. From sketch to colours. Techniques and short cuts i used to paint and general direction. If you are aspiring artist or just appreciate arts and keen to hear more, feel free to drop by!

sessions.title: Dark Souls: The Board Game - Seeking Players
sessions.description: You Died. Just Kidding, come play the table top version of the acclaimed video game. Will you and your companions best the boss or will your flame go out? Up to 4 players, come early to grab a spot. No experience needed.

sessions.title: Furry Feud
sessions.description: Survey says FUN! It's the popular game show featuring furry-centric questions with the top answers on the board. We will need 15 contestants and a whole lot of spectators, so join the fun at Furry Feud!

sessions.title: Dungeoneering Do's and Don'ts
sessions.description: A panel focused on discussing etiquette and other facets of tabletop roleplay games. With a focus on how to be a productive player, tips for new game masters, and ways to find a group to play with.

sessions.title: The Captain Is Dead - Seeking Players
sessions.description:
It's the last ten minutes of your favorite sci-fi show.  Something has gone terribly wrong and the captain is dead!  Be a part of the perilous crew trying to repair the jump core while under attack of an attacking alien fleet.  Will you get the jump core repaired in time or become space dust?

Seats limited on first come basis.

sessions.title: Asexuality in the Furry Fandom
sessions.description: What is asexuality? What does it have to do with being a furry? Join Darby as we explore the ace spectrum and discuss how sexuality can coincide with the furry identity. All allies are welcome!

sessions.title: Meet the Charity
sessions.description: Come and find out all about our guest charity, who they are, what they do, and why we've chosen to support them!

sessions.title: Fursuit Making 101
sessions.description: Ever wanted to make a Fursuit but didn't know where to begin? Well than this is the panel for you! We'll be giving you a crash course on how to make a Fursuit from the head to the tail! And if you already know how to make a Fursuit and want to up your game check out our other panel Fursuit Making 102 where we go more in depth and discuss techniques and tools that professional makers use!

sessions.title: Babyfur & Ageplayer Meet 'n Greet
sessions.description: Babyfurs, lil’furs, caregivers and their bigger friends alike are invited to get together for some friendly cub chatter!  Reconnect with your old friends, meet new one and enjoy some colouring and other cub-friendly activities.  Juice and snacks will be served!

sessions.title: Say Anything - Open Game
sessions.description:
Like Cards Against Humanity? Give Say Anything a try, It's about being as witty, weird, or wild as you want to be! Say Anything offers an opportunity to be creative and have a hilariously good time. 

It's easy to learn and there's no pressure to actually know anything. 'Say anything' you want!
Gather 4 to 8 players. A question is read out loud, such as:

- If you could have a "BIG" anything, what would it be?
- What's the most important invention of the last century?
- Which website would be hardest to live without?
- What's the best activity for a first date?
- What's the worst thing to say to a cop after getting pulled over?

 Players write down their answers. The judge secretly picks a favorite, then everyone else guesses which answer was picked. Points are earned for being chosen by players and the judge. The player with the most points at the end of the game wins!

sessions.title: Chwedlau o'r Tafarn: Welsh Mythology Story Time
sessions.description: In keeping with the theme of the convention, an hour-long session of telling one or two tales from Welsh mythology, in the context of encouraging cross-cultural communication and recognition of our shared human/furry history.

sessions.title: Friday Dance
sessions.description: The one and only panel you don't want to miss! Talented DJs from all over, are guaranteed to get your tails shaking, with non-stop beats!

sessions.title: Furry Improv
sessions.description: Join Dralen, Hiker and Leo for a fun and interactive panel of learn-as-you-go improv games that encourage the audience to jump in feet-first. Warm-ups, quick thinking and memory games will get everyone involved, acting, and laughing. Even if you’re not interested in jumping up on stage, you can contribute with suggestions for the enthusiastic volunteers that join us in front of everyone. Look forward to an exciting night!

sessions.title: Shibari 101: Tying the Knot
sessions.description:
"Learn rope safety and basic ties.

This is for beginners who are interested in beginning their trek in the art of shibari."

sessions.title: Cards Against Humanity - Open Game (18+)
sessions.description:
"Cards Against Humanity is a fill-in-the-blank party game that turns your awkward personality and lackluster social skills into hours of fun! Wow."

An open game session that anyone can drop in and out of; Whether you have a group of your own or are looking for new horrible friends to play with!

Ages 18+, Seating limited on first come basis. See Lounge staff to check out game if one is already not underway.

sessions.title: So Your Gender Melted
sessions.description: For those who have delved into the underpinnings of their gender identity, especially those who know that something needs to change, a forum for sharing successes and pitfalls of dealing with a changing gender identity. A deeper continuation from "Intro to Gender Exploration."

sessions.title: Telestrations After Dark - Open Game (18+)
sessions.description:
One part Pictionary, one part game of Telephone, it's Telestrations! The guess what you see and draw what you read party game!

This is an open game for anyone to join, whether you have you own group or are looking to play with new folks

Learn to play here:
https://youtu.be/OStOnMypEzo

Seats limited up to 8 players, ages 18+ per game on a first come basis. See lounge staff to check out Telestrations if game is not underway.

sessions.title: Tales from the Cellar: Con Horror Stories
sessions.description: Join Conreeaght and guest raconteurs from staff of con's past as we tell stories from the deepest vaults of convention running. All proceeds raised from telling our tales of /redacted/ go to charity. The more you raise, the deeper into the cellar we shall go.

sessions.title: Supersponser Luncheon
sessions.description: Supersponser luncheon as a thank you to our Supersponsors & above tiers.

sessions.title: Flamecraft - Learn to Play
sessions.description:
Learn to play the new Flamecraft board game about Artisan dragons; They are the smaller and magically talented versions of their larger (and destructive) cousins, sought by shopkeepers so that they may delight customers with their flamecraft.

You are a Flamekeeper, skilled in the art of conversing with dragons, placing them in their ideal home and using enchantments to entice them to produce wondrous things. Your reputation will grow as you aid the dragons and shopkeepers, and the Flamekeeper with the most reputation will be known as the Master of Flamecraft.

Seats limited on a first come basis.

For more information on Flamecraft and to find the rulebook, visit:
https://cardboardalchemy.com/flamecraft/

sessions.title: The Elephant in the Room
sessions.description: A panel on bullying among the furry community. (Yes, bullying exists in the community, and also among those over 18.) No naming of bullies; just letting those bullied get it off their chest among others who have gone through the same thing.

sessions.title: Little Canada 3D fursuit scans!
sessions.description: Got get your suit scanned at little canada! With a big group of other furs from the con.

sessions.title: A Private History of Campaigns that Failed.
sessions.description: Throughout history there have been many attempts at starting and maintaining conventions.  While some have succeeded, many have had less than optimum success.  And then there are those whose lack of success have become the stuff of legend.  Here we will examine what happens when well-intentioned people (or, in some cases, less-than-well-intentioned people) get themselves in far over their heads and find out the hard way that it is not always as easy as it looks.

sessions.title: Camel Up - Learn to Play Open Game
sessions.description:
Learn to play the camel racing game where up to eight players bet on five racing camels, trying to suss out which ones will place first and second in a quick race around a pyramid. The earlier you place your bet, the more you can win — should you guess correctly, of course. Camels don't run neatly, however, sometimes landing on top of another one and being carried toward the finish line. Who's going to run when? That all depends on how the dice come out of the pyramid dice shaker, which releases one die at a time when players pause from their bets long enough to see who's actually moving!

How to play: https://youtu.be/5oX4Q7AcpxQ

Seats limited on a first come basis.

sessions.title: Shunned Furries Anonymous
sessions.description: A place where you can freely talk about being bullied, and where you will receive empathy.

sessions.title: Masquerade Rehearsal
sessions.description: Closed-door rehearsal for those trying out for the Masquerade.

sessions.title: Munchkin Tails - Open Game
sessions.description:
Munchkin has gone to the dogs . . . plus foxes, mice, and ponies!

Cute animals have always been popular. (Admit it – you love them.)  Now you can bring them into the dungeon, fighting off foes like the Human Rights Activist, the Robot Vacuum, or even the feared Animal Control Enforcer. Use a Tail Flail or a Cone of Defiance as you work to be the first of your species to reach Level 10!

Limited seats on a first come basis.

sessions.title: Trading Post
sessions.description: Come one, come all!  Have stuff to trade with your fellow furs?  Then come to the Trading Post!  Whether you trade pins, plush, art, or other wares, this is the place to come!  The number one rule is no currency shall be exchanged!

sessions.title: Meet Sanguine Games
sessions.description: Hello world! We’re Sanguine Games. Since the 20th century, We’ve been publishing furry stuff like IRONCLAW, URBAN JUNGLE, USAGI YOJIMBO, and the proverbial more. See photos of our history! Ask questions about our future! And thank you for all these years of helping us share our dreams with you. Hosted by Norman Rafferty.

sessions.title: Furries? In My Anime?!
sessions.description:
"Looking for a new great furry or furry-adjacent anime to watch? What about dipping your paw into the wild world of COSPLAY for the first time?! Zee's got ya covered with over 15 years of anime watching and cosplayin' experience! 

First half of the panel is about anime, second half is tips and tricks for becoming a cosplayer!"

sessions.title: Exploding Kittens - Open Game
sessions.description:
Betray your friends. Try not to explode.
Exploding Kittens is a highly-strategic, kitty powered version of Russian Roulette. Players draw cards until somebody draws an Exploding Kitten, at which point they explode and are out of the game. To avoid exploding, they can defuse the kitten with a laser pointer or catnip sandwich OR use powerful action cards to move or avoid the Exploding Kitten. Betray your friends. Try not to explode. The last player left alive wins. 

Learn More: https://youtu.be/HIpyhhXV_KY

sessions.title: Therianthropy 101
sessions.description: Therianthropy, derived from the Greek therion and anthrōpos refers to beings that are partly human and partly animal, and in this sense is synonymous with the fandom's term furry. It has often been used to describe mythological creatures and deities, and sometimes shortened to "therian," it is today used to describe members of a spiritually oriented subculture.

sessions.title: Transformation (TF) Meet and Greet
sessions.description: Curious about transformation and the TF Fandom more broadly? Well-established and wanting to meet old or new TF friends? Head on down to the TF Meet and Greet to meet like-minded transformation fans and chat with people who share your unique sub-interest(s), or bounce between different groups and get exposed to some fresh new ideas! TF triggers may or may not be included with the panel.

sessions.title: Purple's TikTok fun !
sessions.description:
"Come meet me and have fun with me ! Making tiktoks and making friends ^^ 
All are welcome !! "

sessions.title: Self-Publishing for Beginners
sessions.description: So you want to make a thing? Then you need a plan! We’ll talk you through the process of defining what your thing is, of planning it out, of budgeting and crowd-funding, of marketing and selling, the whole kit and kaboodle. Whether it’s your first novel, your indie video game, your ongoing webcomic, or your boxed tabletop, the basics are all the same. We’ll also talk about fighting anxiety, burnout, and other hobgoblins that can threaten your project and your well-being. Also we’ll answer your questions. Let’s bring your dream to life!

sessions.title: The Captain Is Dead: Lockdown - Seeking Players
sessions.description: After the successful attempt to repair the jump core, the alien fleet has managed to catch up to the perilous crew.  Now they're prisoners on their own ship and need to evade the aliens to regain control and escape.  Fortunately one of their own has defected and is willing to help their cause.  Will you regain control of your ship and escape or decide that a career in space is not for you?

sessions.title: Unstable Unicorns - Open Game
sessions.description:
Unstable Unicorns is a strategic card game about everyone’s two favorite things: Unicorns and Destruction!

The goal of Unstable Unicorns is to be the first person to collect 7 Unicorns in your play area, also known as your Stable. You do this by gathering up your own Unicorn army and using a combination of their magical powers and Magic, Instant, Upgrade, and Downgrade cards to hinder the other players’ progress and destroy their Unicorns instead. But beware -- each player has all of these tools at their disposal as well, and you may just find your plans foiled by a well-played “Neigh!” card.

How to play: https://youtu.be/5yW6VPP_y40

sessions.title: Dragon Tails and Scales of Ontario
sessions.description: Are you a Dragon, a Kobold or even a lizard etc. Then come on down to dragon tails and scales of Ontario where you can meet and greet fellow reptilian brothers and sisters and share interests like what inspired your scale-sona and what media dragons/scalies are featured in and the like of that nature. So if you're a scalie of any kind Alligator, crocodile, salamander etc or maybe you like scalies in general and aren't a scalie yourself. Then if that's the case come on down to Dragon Tails and Scales

sessions.title: How to use money to make more money!
sessions.description: If you've ever wondered how investing works, but you don't quite know what it's all about, this panel is for you! We'll go over the basic terms, what they mean, how the stock market works, and give some useful advice on how to get started, all in a simple and enjoyable format so even a simple moose can understand it!

sessions.title: Warrior Cats Panel
sessions.description: Warrior cats was an awakening for a lot of Furries, come join Gray, Scout, and Rae to dive into the world Warrior cats. Talking about our favorite characters, clans, and come take part in a trivia game with questions from both series one two!

sessions.title: Fur Azeroth!
sessions.description:
"Aka'Magosh. Are you for the Horde? For the Alliance?  Come pull up a chair by the Hearth and chat with Worgens, Vulperas & Dracthyrs! (Oh my!) 

Talk about your favourite classes/races, expansions, achievement bragging rights, your incredible mount drop luck and/or exchange Battle.net ID's with other fellow champions of Azeroth!  Lok'tar Ogar!"

sessions.title: Tour de Fur
sessions.description: Join us on a scenic tour of Toronto's historic waterfront! Prepare to wave to many passers by and get ready for some gorgeous photo opportunities as we strut our stuff along Lakeshore this year.

sessions.title: King of Tokyo - Open Game
sessions.description:
Play mutant monsters, gigantic robots and other monstrous creatures, rampaging the city and vying for position as the one and only King of Tokyo!

Combine your dice to gather energy, heal your monster or just slap the other monsters down! Spend your energy to trigger permanent or one-shot special powers: a second head, body armor, nova death ray...

Stop at nothing to become the King of Tokyo... but that's when the real trouble begins for you!

sessions.title: Cassidy Civet in Concert
sessions.description: You may have seen her on Canada's Got Talent last year, or even at Eurovision, but now the fandom's premier Pop music princess is in Toronto at her first Furnal Equinox ready to deliver a full fursuit spectacular of original furry music! With all her hits and previews of her upcoming second album, it's sure to be a show you won't wanna miss! Find all her music online by searching "Cassidy Civet"!

sessions.title: Mario Strikers: Battle League World Cup
sessions.description: Do you like Mario? Do you like FutBall? Do you like Video Games? Why not come on down and press your luck in our Tag Team Mario Strikerz Battle League World Cup Tournament. To enter you must have a partner. There are 16 slots *8 teams* if you do not have a partner one will be assigned to you. Each tier in the tournament will be run as a series. Tier A will be best 3/5 Tier B will be best 3/5 and our world cup final will be best 4/7. Prizes: To those who lose in our semi-final they will have a one game 3rd place battle. To our third place winners you will get $20 ($10 each). To our Mushroom League and Koopa League champions who make it to the world cup final. Second place will be $60 ($30 each) and last but especially not least our first place grand champions will receive not only a $140 ($70 each) prize, BUT free Sponsor level registration to Furnal Equinox 2024 on the house of the Host of the tournament. So hope you're able to come to our Strikerz battle league tournament and that you have a grand time

sessions.title: Protogen/Synth Meet n' Greet
sessions.description: A meet up for protogens, synths or other robotic like beep boops!

sessions.title: Uncle Kage's Story Hour
sessions.description: Uncle Kage has been telling stories on stage at Furry conventions for more than a quarter century, and as long as there is a glass of wine within reach, he's likely to keep doing so.  His stories cover everything from the people he's encountered during his travels to odd circumstances he's either witnessed or endured on his own, and are all assured to be 105% true.

sessions.title: The Owl House Fan Meetup
sessions.description: A panel to hang out with and meet other fans of the popular Disney channel show, The Owl House! There will likely be merch giveaways, games, chatting and colouring at the meetup!

sessions.title: Magic: The Gathering - Open Gaming
sessions.description:
Calling all Magic: The Gathering players!

A casual event for Magic playing attendees of Furnal Equinox to meet other Magic: The Gathering enthusiasts and find new opponents to duel.

All formats welcome, but Casual and Commander suggested.

This is social gaming event with no host or lead and will take place at the reserved, rectangular tables located in the rear-most (Pier 5) section of the Lounge (Pier 4 & 5.)

sessions.title: The Olden Days – The History of Furry Fandom from One Who Lived Them
sessions.description: Presented by someone whose first exposure to Furry Fandom was in 1989.  Now that he's an old guy, he can sit on the porch and reminisce about how things were ‘way back when, in the days when fursuits were a rarity and FurryMuck was the primary gathering spot for furries worldwide.

sessions.title: VRChat Meet-and-Greet
sessions.description:
Plug in! Log on! Let's get virtual in reality!

Join Chevron and mBlade for Furnal Equinox's first ever VRChat meet-and-greet panel. Whether you're brand-new to the VR scene or a longtime "Trusted User," join us to link up with friends from across the digital divide and chat about all the amazing things you can do in VRChat. Learn about everything from raves to games to chillout worlds, all of the fun groups of friends and furs you can meet along the way, and even building your own world and avatar.

We are VR!

sessions.title: Furnal Equinox's Masquerade
sessions.description: A live talent show, showcasing the fandoms amazing and diverse talents. Singers and musicians, comedians and performers showcase their talents to try and earn their name on our Masquerade Cup.

sessions.title: Twister - Open Games
sessions.description:
Give the spinner a whirl and see what’s next as you try to keep your hands and feet on the mat! Right foot red! Can you do it? Left foot green… you got it! If your knee or elbow touches the mat, or you fall over, you’re out. Be the last player standing to win! TWISTER game challenges you to put your hands and feet at different places on the mat without falling over! Be the last player standing to win.

Fursuit Friendly!

sessions.title: Drawing Pokemon from Memory
sessions.description: You may remember all their names, but can you remember all of their markings? Join me for a fun session of trying to draw out pokemon solely from memory! No refsheets, no looking up pokemon, just trying to pull from your memory bank what these pokemon look like! All artist skill levels welcome and encouraged to participate! Will provide paper and drawing supplies!

sessions.title: Pin Trading Panel
sessions.description: Curious about all the hype of collecting and trading pins? Come by and witness it first hand! Don’t have a pin to trade with? NaysPinClub will provide you with a free starter pin! You can keep it, or trade it around until you are happy with what you have!

sessions.title: De-tail re-tail: stories of those in retail
sessions.description:
"Stories and sharing of those in trail weather it be something out of the ordinary or something awesome!

Depending on the stories. Listener discression is advised."

sessions.title: Convention War Stories
sessions.description: Many convention-goers remain blissfully unaware of the horrors that sometimes take place behind the scenes of a convention.  Hear some of the secret testimony of the miserable souls who survived these terrifying ordeals

sessions.title: Super Smash Bros. Ultimate Tournament
sessions.description:
Super Smash Bros. Ultimate Tournament hosted by Seika Skye

Regular Tournament rules applied (3 stocks 7 minutes, Tourney legal stages only, best of 3 wins), there will be a loser's bracket for a chance to make a comeback as well as a prize pot! 

Please register at the Gaming Lounge Monday or Saturday at any time.
Please be present at the gaming lounge 15-30 minutes before the event starts.
All skill levels are welcome!

sessions.title: Captian Sonar - Open Game
sessions.description:
Captain sonar is an innovative real-time game that challenges two teams to take their submarines head-to-head in a thrilling battle. Your ultimate goal is to find and destroy your opponent's submarine, but this task is far more difficult that it may first appear. Your entire crew must work together to chart a course, charge systems, locate the enemy, and keep your own submarine fully operational. Communication and teamwork can lead you to victory, but if you fail to cooperate, you'll be sunk to the bottom of the ocean!

Come and join some Captain Sonar, whether solo or a team of 4. Seats limited to 8 players on a first come basis.

sessions.title: Cutthroat Artist
sessions.description: It's a showdown of four talented artists who will compete in timed surprise art challenges featuring subjects chosen from our audience. Each round, one artist will be eliminated by our judge until the winner is crowned! The catch? Artists can bid on sabotages to inflict on their competitors. Scheduled to compete: NicNak, Kari Pup, Lilac Ounce & Stan the Lion. May the most cutthroat competitor win!

sessions.title: Fursuit care 101- Tips and tricks to maintain your suit
sessions.description: Come one come all and learn how to keep that giant animal rug looking fresh. Hear from an established fursuit maker about cleaning, storage and general care tips for all kinds of fursuits

sessions.title: Wildlife Rescue Workshop
sessions.description: Come and learn about how you can help out with wildlife rescue with the Hobbitstee Wildlife Refuge.

sessions.title: Red Dragon Inn - Open Game
sessions.description:
You can't have Tales from the Tavern without the tavern!

The long-running Red Dragon Inn series is the hilarious card game about what the adventurers do after the adventure. Each player takes the role of a different character at the party at the tavern as they drink, gamble and roughhouse with each other. The last standing during this evening of fun is the winner!

How to Play: https://youtu.be/EifIbl4XKTM

Seats may be limited, on a first come basis. No actual drinking or gambling permitted.

sessions.title: The Bird Meet :>
sessions.description: "A meet and greet for birds and their friends~"

sessions.title: Supervillain Meet'n'greet
sessions.description: Ever wanted to be a supervillain? Maybe wondered what's up with those furs with pink visors, rayguns, and queer mayhem? Come join your fellow caped cacklers and humorous henches for a meet-and-greet, hosted by ambassadors of the Digital Villainy Summit, an online convention celebrating its fifth year in August 2023!

sessions.title: Art Jam with Anyare
sessions.description: Bring you sketchbooks, Tablets, and more for a fun interactive drawing session with Anyare.

sessions.title: Tales from the Tavern Jeopardy!
sessions.description: All great journeys end in the tavern, and the knowledge you’ve gleaned listening to adventurers’ tales over pints might not seem unimportant.  That is, until you find yourself matched against two fierce rivals in a classic answer & question contest.  Draw from your trove of high culture and pop culture knowledge and wager carefully to become this year’s Jeopardy! champion.  A quiz before the show will determine the three contestants, but stick around no matter what because they just might need your help if they get stumped!  Prizes will be awarded to all contestants!

sessions.title: Saturday Dance
sessions.description: The one and only panel you don't want to miss! Talented DJs from all over, are guaranteed to get your tails shaking, with non-stop beats!

sessions.title: The Dragstravaganza! Hosted by Alissa Brink & Bear Sailor Moon
sessions.description:
"We are BACK BACK BACK BACK BACK AGAIN! The Dragstravaganza with Alissa Brink & Bear SailorMoon! Come join us for an evening of incredible drag. Whether its your first time ever seeing a drag show or you've lost track of how many drag bars you've been in ALL ARE WELCOME!
Get ready to Cheer, Gasp, Laugh and Scream!"

sessions.title: Late Night Tavern Tales - D&D 5th Edition
sessions.description: Come play in a spooky themed game of Dungeons and Dragons. Game-master Valrus will take you on an adventure late into the evening as you try to unravel a haunting mystery. Pre-generated Characters, up to 5 players. D&D 5th edition rules, no experience needed.

sessions.title: Cards Against Humanity - Open Game (18+)
sessions.description:
"Cards Against Humanity is a fill-in-the-blank party game that turns your awkward personality and lackluster social skills into hours of fun! Wow."

An open game session that anyone can drop in and out of; Whether you have a group of your own or are looking for new horrible friends to play with!

Ages 17+, Seating limited on first come basis. See Lounge staff to check out game if one is already not underway.

sessions.title: Puppy/Pet Play 101
sessions.description: Have you ever wanted to be a puppy? Have you ever felt like just barking at something or someone? Ever want to get down on all fours and chase around a ball? Or ever just been fascinated with a squeaky toy? Then unleash your inner pup and join us as we explore the wonderful and ever-growing world of pup/pet play. We will take you on a journey into the mind of a pup/pet as we discuss and answer the questions of - What is pup/pet play? Where did it all start? How are puppies and furries different? How are they similar? Why become a pup/pet? What is headspace? What is a handler and what do they do? How do I get started/involved? We'll also cover important safety aspects, basic etiquette, guidelines to follow, and the gear you may see.

sessions.title: The Vore Panel
sessions.description: What is vore? Why do people enjoy being swallowed alive? More importantly, why is it in every cartoon and piece of media? Come learn in a safe environment with this comedic and informative presentation hosted by Marshmallow, now updated with new slides and examples!

sessions.title: Charity Auction
sessions.description: Come and raise money for our wonderful charity by bidding on works of art!

sessions.title: Fursuit Repairs and Maintenance
sessions.description: Learn how to do minor repairs and upkeep on your fursuit along with discussing different building methods.

sessions.title: Paleoart 101: Bringing Prehistoric Animals To Life
sessions.description: Ever wanted to bring dinosaurs back from the dead without the risk of starting a biological apocalypse? You’re in luck! This panel will cover the basic principles of paleoart to help you approach drawing extinct animals in new and creative ways.

sessions.title: Being a Rogue
sessions.description: A panel to teach those that are interested in locks and lock-picking, bypassing and some real physical security knowledge.

sessions.title: Asexuality: Finding and Understanding Oneself
sessions.description: There are many myths and facts about Asexuality. It can often come across as confusing, scary, intimidating etc. But breaking it down to the simplest form of understanding is key to accepting either yourself or your friends or your partner. Come join this discussion as we do a crash course in being Asexual and how amazing it is!

sessions.title: Everdell - Learn to Play Open Game
sessions.description: Come and learn to play the fantastically cute board game of Everdell! Compete to build the best village full of woodland residents. No experience needed. Come early to grab a spot, up to 6 players!

sessions.title: Creating Comics
sessions.description: Want to know more about creating comics? Are you a writer looking for an artist? Don't know where to start posting? Join TylerMannArt / Marshmallow for a little help getting started in the world of writing, drawing, and making comics! Presentation followed by a Q+A!

sessions.title: Artemis Spaceship Bridge Simulator (Presented by Hacklab Toronto)
sessions.description:
Artemis is a real time Co-Op computer game. Players work together in the roles of Captain, Helm, Science, Communication, Engineering, and Weapon Control. Operate the ship, take on missions and defend against other hostile ships.

New and experienced players welcome. Drop in for a pick-up game, or register your crew for a group session.

Present by Hacklab Toronto
https://hacklab.to/

Artemis Spaceship Bridge Simulator
https://www.artemisspaceshipbridge.com/

sessions.title: Rodents!
sessions.description: Come all ye Rodents, friend gnawers in need of a good chew!  We gather to discuss what we love about being Rodents, and anything about them we love, be it stories, art, games, or even keeping of pet Rodents.  We'll have a group photo for all Rodent fursuiters at the end.

sessions.title: So you want to work in Animation
sessions.description: Do you have an interest in breaking into the animation industry? Come get the lowdown on the industry from long time veterans who have worked in TV, Games and Feature Film. Find out what options for education and possible career paths.

sessions.title: The Reckoners - Seeking Players
sessions.description: Radiation from a strange object has given a small group of humans superpowers and invincibility.  Led by Steelheart, these super humans known as Epics, have taken over the city of Chicago now known as Newcago.  An elite group known as The Reckoners, led by the Prof, must learn the weaknesses of the Epics and Steelheart in order to free Newcago from their reign.  Do you have what it takes to be a Reckoner?

sessions.title: I Came, I Staffed, I Had the Best Con of My Life
sessions.description: It's true — many con staff go on to enjoy the cons they staff at even more than they did before staffing! Join Avalanche and some of your favorite FE staff for a discussion on what it means to be staff, how we came to be here, and how staffing might make your con experiences even more fun and engaging!

sessions.title: Video Creators Social
sessions.description: Do you make Tiktoks or YouTube videos? Are you otherwise involved in the production of video content? This panel is a place to meet other creators in the furry community to talk about the process of creating video media of all types, and connect with creators. This is an unstructured, open-ended social environment to compare notes, plan collaborations, and discuss the joys and frustrations of video creation on any platform.

sessions.title: Producing with Hexagon Jack
sessions.description: In this panel hexagon Jack will be teaching you the basics of music production.  Such as how to use synths how to make a drop and even a track breakdown.

sessions.title: Bronies Forever
sessions.description: Bronies and Pegasisters are invited to come chat with their fellow fans of My Little Pony.  "Friendship is Magic" may have concluded, but the pony fan community has found new life with two new series: “Make Your Mark” and “Tell Your Tale.”  Maybe you have a favourite "remember when?" moment from the past series to reminisce about or you have some exciting theories over what will happen to the new generation of equines?  You bring a topic, and we provide the banter!

sessions.title: Closing Ceremonies
sessions.description: The opening ceremonies and closing ceremonies

sessions.title: Dead Dog
sessions.description: The one and only panel you don't want to miss! Talented DJs from all over, are guaranteed to get your tails shaking, with non-stop beats!

sessions.title: "So You Want to Run a Furry Event"
sessions.description: Join FE Chair Avalanche and Anthropomorphic Events of Ontario Chair Scani to talk about the ins and outs of running a furry event!

An upcomer in the furry music scene, Cassidy made her brief debut with the release of her debut album "Double Take" at the end February 2020, just before the pandemic. Now confined to her home, she has pivoted to online concerts to get her music heard. Being a proud POC creator, her unique voice and perspective is one to be heard. You can find her on Twitter and Youtube, with her music available on most streaming services, with CDs exclusive through Bandcamp.
speakers.tagLine: Furry Musician with a new album out now!

speakers.bio: Chantal founded Hobbitstee Wildlife Refuge in 2007 and since it has grown into a wildlife rehab facility who rehabilitates 3000 plus wild animals a year. Chantal still runs the organization as the PIC and is the Authorized Wildlife Custodian on record for this fully licensed wildlife facility.

Chevron is a gray wolf, gamer, and event host from New Jersey. He works with several VRChat-based convention groups like Tailbass, Vibe Night, SnelRev Events, and xCirrex Media to bring people together for fun nights, games, friendship, and great times. He hosts Thursday VRChat Games every week, as well as in-person gatherings monthly, and passionately embraces VRChat and its rave and convention scene, especially with Furnal Equinox and the Furality Online Xperience. You'll find him most often taking pictures and sharing them on his art galleries to help promote events and organizations. His team co-hosted Furrydelphia's first ever VRChat Meet-and-Greet and Intro Panel, and he is now working to set up VRChat portals and meets at other in-person conventions.

Chevron's love and passion for Furnal Equinox motivated him to cosplay as "Badgie" (Virtual Furnal Equinox 2021's unofficial mascot made of nothing but attendee badges) at the in-person convention in 2022.

A lifelong player of EVE Online, Mechwarrior, Armed Assault III, Halo, and Command & Conquer, Chevron holds a particular appreciation for older games of the late 1990s-early 2000s. He shows off his admiration of cyberpunk by wearing an LED visor from Illumi Cyberwear. His fursuit was made by Sarahcat. Outside of the fandom, he works in the IT industry as a cybersecurity administrator.

Chevron's ultimate goal is to bring people together for fun and great times. He embraces the future with open arms and is eager to dive right into all the fun that can be had together with friends and the fandom.
speakers.tagLine: Boot up! Plug in! Let's play! We are VR!

speakers.bio: Blue and White wolf (Not Husky!) From Ottawa, Ontario, Canada, Loves Board Games and making Friends. Co-Chair of CanFurence. He/him
I've been active in the fandom since 2006 as a fursuiter.

Dragon/Doggo

When he isn't working in Cardiff, Dai enjoys a good read, a leisurely cycle ride, or time well spent in good company.

Dralen has been a furry since the early 90's, and has been co-hosting improv at furry events like Camp Feral and Furnal Equinox since the late 00's. He is a freelance voice actor that focuses mostly on audiobooks, and has a YouTube channel about food.

You can follow them @darbington on FA or Instagram, or @joeywontshutup on twitter.

Hello my name is Darryl Malloy or also known as Miles The Fox online!

Hey i am Flow and i have bin in the fandom for 10+ years now. I love running local events and making new friends. You will definitely hear me before you see me. "Samuel Conway is a chemist who holds a Ph.D. from Dartmouth and works in a laboratory in the Research Triangle area of North Carolina.  He is also the chairman of Anthrocon, the world's largest Furry convention, held annually in Pittsburgh, PA.  Known as "Uncle Kage" to his fans, he is an experienced raconteur who has performed on stage all around the country and even in such far-flung places as Germany, Australia, England and even the Czech Republic.  He has been called by some an unofficial spokesperson for the Furry fandom since he has dedicated a good deal of time and energy to dispelling the myths and misconceptions surrounding the world of anthropomorphics.  In what spare time he can find he likes to write and has published a number of stories in small-press titles, although he did break into the Big World in 1999 when his story "Tweaked in the Head" was included in "Flights of Fantasy," an anthology of bird-related SF tales assembled by Mercedes Lackey.  He has since published stories in Ms. Lackey’s 2012 "Elemental Magic" and 2013 “Elementary” anthologies, and in Fred Patten’s “The Furry Future” and “Gods with Fur.”
